[經濟類]社區期票 1.0 體系提案 07 & 08 May 2024
1. 期票泛指：
  a. 以資源類方塊作量化抵押品的票據；
  b. 以非資源類方塊作量化抵押品的票據；
  c. 以生存模式裏可自然獲取的遊戲物品，作可量化抵押品的票據；
  d. 以管理員之任意定製遊戲物品作可量化抵押品的票據；以及
  e. 以管理員受認可之任意遊戲內物品作可量化抵押品的票據。

2. 任何票據、期票，需具有以下特徵：
  a. 由相應數量的抵押品支持；
  b. 具有對掛鉤抵押品的兌換力；
  c. 相關抵押品具有透明的，可由任何玩家監視的流通量；
  d. 不可複製性；以及
  e. 資本市場機制運作下的自由流通力。

3.期票對應的抵押品單位：
  a. 可疊類物品(Stackable Items)：
  “Set”/“Stack” - 即一格物品欄內，自身最大自然疊加量是16-64個的物品；
  1 Set - 對應A類期票；
  2 Set - 對應B類期票；

  (i)/1張B類期票可換2張A類期票。
  (ii)/期票1.0裏期票最大面額為B類期票。

  b. 不可疊類物品(Non-stackable Items):
  “Unit” -  即一格物品欄內，自身最大容量只能為1個的物品
  1 Unit - 對應Z類期票；

(i)/期票1.0裏不可疊加類期票最大面額為Z類期票。

4. 管理員保留最終裁定權。
------------------------------------------
English Translation:
A Draft Proposal On Item-Backed Term Bill （ITB） Trading | Version 1.0

1. An Item-Backed Term Bill ("ITB" in short) refers to:
  a. A Note/Bill backed by resource blocks;
  b. A Note/Bill backed by non-resource blocks;
  c. A Note/Bill backed by naturally obtainable items in survival mode;
  d. A Note/Bill backed by any customised items forged by the moderator; and
  e. A Bote/Bill backed by any quantifiable in-game items, which must be verified and recognised by the moderator.

2. Any Item-Backed Term Bills must contain the following characteristics:
  a. Backed by its collateral;
  b. Has the fixed exchange value designated to the amount of collaterals;
  c. The collaterals is under a transparent, trackable volume trading which can be monitored by any players;
  d. Non-Fungible/Anti-counterfeiting; and
  e. Free liquidity under the market mechanism of the player base.

3. Unit size of the collaterals:
  a. Stackable items:
  "Set(s)"/"Stack(s)" refers to the maximum capacity of an item slot that can naturally store the item (16 to 64)
  e.g. Snowball has a natural maximum stackable capacity of 16 in one item slot; cobblestone has a natural maximum stackable capacity of 64 in one item slot.
  
  1 Set/1 Stack - One unit of type A ITB;
  2 Sets/2 Stacks - Two units of type B ITB.

  (i)/Two units of type A ITBs have a fixed exchange rate to One unit of type B ITB;
  (ii)/Version 1.0 of ITB trading allows type B ITB to be legally the maximum face value for stackable items.

  b. Non-stackable items:
  "unit" refers to the refers to the monopolistic capacity of an item slot that can naturally store the item.
  1 unit - 1 unit of type Z ITB;

(i)/Version 1.0 of ITB trading allows type Z ITB to be legally the maximum face value for non-stackable items.

4. All rights to arbitration and articulation are reserved to the moderator.
